# The @siteimprove/* Alfa (Siteimprove) ACT-Rules packages are published to the
# public npm registry, so no scope routing or auth token is needed — npm resolves
# them from the default registry like any other dependency.
#
# They are declared as OPTIONAL dependencies in package.json, so if the registry
# is ever unreachable, `npm ci` / `npm install` skips them WITHOUT failing the
# build and the Alfa runner degrades to a no-op (dynamic import + try/catch).
# See engine.ts runAlfa.
